                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d385">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/681: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Swenson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-14T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >December 14, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 14—11:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>21. Department’s circular of December 5, 4 p.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d385fn10">Not
                        printed.</note> After conferring with Foreign Offices of the other
                    Scandinavian countries, the Norwegian <pb facs="0566" n="422" xml:id="pg_422"/>
                    Government feels that in view of agreement entered into between Soviet and
                    Chinese Governments the suggested representations would seem inopportune.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Swenson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
